Fausta Garavini (Bologna, 1938) is an Italian writer and translator. She studied French and Occitan literature at the University of Florence[1] She later worked as a literature professor at this university and as a essayist in several publications like "Paragone", "Nuovi Argomenti", "Revue d'histoire littraire de la France" and "Littrature". y 
